# Slice 003J: Background Job Scheduling Foundation

## Status
Not Started

## Parent Epic
Epic 003: Audit, Documents, Config, and Dashboard Foundation
Epic file: `docs/epics/003-audit-documents-config-foundation.md`

## Goal
Add a minimal backend background-job scheduling foundation that later slices can use for reminders,
async reports, and notification generation without sending real communications or running external
workers in this slice.

## User Value
Moves the platform one verifiable step closer to a working end-to-end lending system without broad module-sized changes.

## Depends On
- 003IA2

## Source References
- docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md sections 10, 20-22
- docs/source/api-contracts.md sections 26, 39, 41, 42-43
- docs/source/data-model.md document/config/audit tables
- docs/source/component-spec.md
- docs/source/design-system.md

## Prototype Reference
- sfpcl-lms/src/pages/Dashboard.tsx
- sfpcl-lms/src/pages/tasks/TaskInbox.tsx
- sfpcl-lms/src/components/loan/AuditTimeline.tsx
- sfpcl-lms/src/components/loan/DocumentPackModal.tsx

## Screens Involved
None directly.

## Frontend Scope
None for this slice, except updating frontend documentation or fixtures if required by tests.

## Backend/API Scope
Implement only a local scheduler/job metadata shell:
- A model for scheduled jobs with source-neutral fields: job id, job type/code, status, due/run time,
  related entity type/id when applicable, attempts, last error summary, created/updated timestamps.
- A small service boundary to enqueue a job idempotently and mark it running/succeeded/failed for
  future modules.
- No Celery/Redis/cloud scheduler dependency unless already pinned and importable.
- No real email/SMS/courier delivery, no reminder generation business rules, no report generation,
  and no automatic notification creation beyond what 003IA already does for communication sends.
- Keep the scheduler service in its own backend module/app boundary. Do not add scheduler state,
  transition logic, or retry handling into `sfpcl_credit.communications.services`.
- Do not touch notification mark-read behavior in this slice; `003IA2` owns the atomic
  `read_state_version` hardening before scheduler work starts.
- Treat 003IA2 as complete: scheduler tests should assert they do not change
  `/api/v1/notifications/{notification_id}/mark-read/` semantics, create notification read-state
  rows, or write `communications.notification.marked_read` audit rows.
- If the slice adds only an internal service boundary, prefer no public scheduler endpoint. If an
  endpoint is necessary, keep it under its own scheduler/admin path and document it separately from
  `/api/v1/dashboard/`, `/api/v1/notifications/`, and `/api/v1/communications/`.

## Database/Model Impact
Non-destructive model/migration changes for this capability, if needed.

## API Contracts
If an endpoint is added, record it in `docs/working/API_CONTRACTS.md` with standard envelopes,
strict query validation, and top-level pagination. Keep it clearly separate from
`/api/v1/dashboard/`, `/api/v1/notifications/`, and `/api/v1/communications/`.

## Permissions
Use the narrowest existing administrative/ops permission. If source docs do not name a scheduler
permission, record the assumption in `ASSUMPTIONS.md`; do not reuse communication-send or dashboard
permissions for scheduler administration.

## Audit Requirements
Audit metadata-only scheduler mutations if exposed through an API. Do not audit raw rendered
message bodies, provider payloads, or report contents.

## Validation Rules
Validate job type/status values, related entity UUIDs, idempotency keys if supported, and legal
state transitions. Do not invent reminder timing, report cadence, or notification business rules.

## Test Cases
- Service tests for enqueue idempotency and legal/illegal status transitions.
- Service test proving enqueue idempotency is atomic for the chosen idempotency key or natural key;
  duplicate enqueue attempts should not create duplicate runnable rows.
- API tests, if an endpoint is added, for `401`, `403`, strict query validation, pagination, and no
  provider side effects.
- Regression test that dashboard tasks and notification inbox rows are not generated by the
  scheduler shell in this slice.
- Regression test that enqueue idempotency does not depend on notification `read_state_version` or
  communication send/list behavior; this slice should not import from
  `sfpcl_credit.communications.services` except through stable, already-existing public APIs.

## Visual Acceptance Criteria
None.

## Evidence Required
Test output, API response examples, and screenshots when frontend is touched.

## Risk Level
Medium

## Acceptance Criteria
- The named capability works through the intended backend/API/frontend path, where applicable.
- Source-doc business rules are enforced or documented as assumptions.
- Permissions and audit expectations are tested when applicable.
- The implementation stays within one small Ralph slice.

## Done Checklist
- [ ] Execution plan written
- [ ] Tests written or updated
- [ ] Code implemented
- [ ] API contracts updated, if needed
- [ ] Database rules followed, if needed
- [ ] Permissions tested, if needed
- [ ] Audit events tested, if needed
- [ ] Visual evidence saved, if frontend
- [ ] Tests/typecheck/lint/build passed
- [ ] Risk assessment completed
- [ ] Handoff updated
- [ ] State updated
- [ ] Commit created only after passing gates

